My intent was to make it visible that the code should not fail. I'm not a fan of tests without assertions. I will write it like this instead:
        try {
            user.push.registerDevice(SAMPLE_TOKEN, SERVICE_NAME).blockingGetResult()
        } catch (e: Exception) {
            fail(e.message)
        }

This way we can still see the reason why it failed if it does fail - which shouldn't.

